    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Filago perpusilla are anti-inflammatory and antiseptic effects, which make it useful in wound healing and the treatment of skin conditions. The antiseptic properties of this plant also contribute to its ability to prevent infections and promote tissue repair, while its antioxidant properties help protect against cell damage and oxidative stress, ultimately leading to a reduction in the risk of chronic diseases such as cancer and cardiovascular disease. The anti-inflammatory properties of Filago perpusilla also make it useful in the treatment of respiratory issues, such as bronchitis and asthma, by reducing inflammation and improving lung function. The antimicrobial properties of this plant also contribute to its ability to prevent the growth of microorganisms, which makes it useful in the treatment of infections and the prevention of the spread of diseases. The antiproliferative properties of Filago perpusilla also make it useful in the treatment of cancer by inhibiting the growth of cancer cells and promoting apoptosis.",
