    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Filago perpusilla are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and terpenoids which are responsible for its medicinal properties. Flavonoids present in Filago perpusilla have antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities that contribute to its healing effects. Phenolic acids such as ferulic acid and caffeic acid exhibit anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which help in wound healing and protection against infections. Terpenoids, including sesquiterpenes and diterpenes, have been found to possess anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antitumor activities, which may be beneficial in treating various health conditions. These bioactive compounds work synergistically to provide the medicinal benefits associated with Filago perpusilla.",
