    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Filago perpusilla are derived from its leaves and flowers due to their rich content of flavonoids and phenolic acids. Infusion is made by steeping the plant material in hot water to release its bioactive compounds which have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Filago perpusilla tea is prepared in a similar manner but with a lower water temperature to preserve its volatile compounds which have been shown to possess antimicrobial activity. Tincture is prepared by steeping the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated liquid extract that can be used to make salves and ointments. Salves and ointments are topical preparations made by mixing the tincture with a carrier oil or wax to create a semi-solid formulation that can be applied to the skin to treat wounds and skin irritations due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties.",
